{
  "stem": "15174.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But you know, we were constantly afraid because we knew-- we heard the news, the Germans were attacking Russia, and God only knew when they were going to take over all of France.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You know we just wanted to get out of Europe, away from-- from the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, Southern France I told you was, quote 'free' or Vichy France, and as such had diplomatic relations with the United States.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The consulate was in Marseille.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So my father was able to go to this consulate and-- and ask about our visa number to the United States and pursue that, which was extremely fortunate.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because in the Spring of 1942 we-- we-- our number came up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We got a visa to the United States, which was wonderful, except for one thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was in the middle of the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How were we going to get to the United States?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean there were no planes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only way to go was a boat, but it was the middle of the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where were you gonna get a boat?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the only place-- the only two countries in-- well, there were three countries, actually, in Europe that were neutral, and those countries were Sweden, Spain-- Spain had just gone through the Civil War, so they weren't interested in joining any other war-- Spain, and Portugal.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the only ship that you could go on would be a neutral ship because if you went on a French ship it was very dangerous that you might be fired on by U-boats.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So anyway, we actually managed to get passage on a ship from Portugal leaving Lisbon for the United States in-- at the end of-- that was at the end of May or the middle of May of 1942.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
